		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Changes For Wizards? Absor Speaks Out</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=381554" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Absor responded to a concerned wizard on the boards. View the thread <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/062802.html" target="_blank">here</a>.
<blockquote>
Calvarro wrote:<br>
You know VI could go a long way towards placating us just by posting one simple sentence:<br>
"Yes, we are making some positive changes to wizards."
<p>
They don't even have to say what they are, just that they are actually doing them. So far I have seen just about every class get improvement, or have improvement scheduled for them, except Wizard.
<P>
Come on, Absor, Abashi.. just that one little sentence.
<p>
<b>
Yes, we are making some positive changes to wizards.
<p>
Alan
<p>
I'm not being flippant. It's true. But you'll just have to be a little patient.
</b>
</blockquote>

		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
